            "body": "This issue can only be reproduced on Windows 10 and has been [addressed](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/console/closepseudoconsole#remarks) on Windows 11.\n\nBTW, @zshoals, curious did you have any good workaround for cleaning them up before? :)\nI tried cleaning up `conhost` using `VimLeave + jobstart/detach + powershell/nvim`, but those were sometimes not invoked, then I ask gpt to write a small c prog instead, which works well:\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('VimLeave', {\n    callback = function()\n        local pids = vim.api.nvim_get_proc_children(vim.fn.getpid())\n        if #pids <= 2 then return end\n        -- sleep 1000ms, then terminate conhost.exe\n        local args = vim.list_extend({[[E:\\workspace\\test\\demo.exe]], 1000}, pids)\n        vim.fn.jobstart(args, {detach = true})\n\tend\n})\n```\n```c\n#include <stdio.h>\n#include <windows.h>\n\nvoid kill(DWORD pid) {\n    HANDLE h = OpenProcess(PROCESS_TERMINATE | PROCESS_QUERY_LIMITED_INFORMATION, FALSE, pid);\n    if (!h) return;\n    char path[MAX_PATH];\n    DWORD size = sizeof(path);\n    if (!QueryFullProcessImageNameA(h, 0, path, &size)) return;\n    char *name = strrchr(path, '\\\\');\n    if (_stricmp(name + 1, \"conhost.exe\") != 0) return;\n    TerminateProcess(h, 1);\n    CloseHandle(h);\n}\n\nint main(int argc, char **argv) {\n    Sleep(atoi(argv[1]));\n    for (int i = 2; i < argc; i++) {\n        DWORD pid = (DWORD)atoi(argv[i]);\n        if (pid) kill(pid);\n    }\n    return 0;\n}\n```",
